# Global Terrorism Data from 1970 through 2015

The GTD includes systematic data on domestic as well as transnational and international terrorist incidents that have occurred during this time period and now includes more than 150,000 cases. For each GTD incident, information is available on the date and location of the incident, the weapons used and nature of the target, the number of casualties, and--when identifiable--the group or individual responsible. The data include items, such as:

   * Year, Month, day: time information of terrorist incidents
   * county: numeric code with country name following
   * region: numeric code with region name following
   * specificity: the geospatial resolution of the latitude and longitude fields. The most specific resolution uniformly available throughout the dataset is the center of the city, village, or town in which the attack occurred
   * vicinity: The incident occurred in the immediate vicinity of the city in
   question or not
   * summary: description of the incident
   
...

For more specific variables and corresponding code information, please refer to the attached Codebook.pdf

Source: The Global Terrorism Database (GTD) http://www.start.umd.edu/gtd/about/
